narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor define the topic of study?
How clearly did the instructor outline the expectation for the course, classroom activity and homework?
comments: I did not receive any feedback on the submissions I failed to submit.

narratives.question_text: How well were individual class sessions prepared and presented?
How well did lectures fit within the boundaries of the course?
comments: I think it should be more than 2h a week and to go deeper into machinery design.
Right amount of homework... maybe should be a little more challenging

narratives.question_text: How available was the instructor for help outside the classroom?
How useful were assignments in furthering an understanding of the topic?
comments: The assignments helped me review what we would discuss in class. but I still feel unsure about my knowledge of application.

narratives.question_text: If tests were given, how fairly did they measure knowledge gained?
comments: the tests were pretty easy to answer as they followed the rubric of the examples and the review sheets. no preparation was required. which made me feel unsure about how comfortable I had got about the concepts.

narratives.question_text: How useful was this course in preparing you for production work?
comments: I didnt get to use the knowledge in my production assignment yet but I got the general idea of components of winch and how to design the system given the criteria

narratives.question_text: How would you evaluate the instructor's knowledge of the material?
comments: He is a pillar of knowledge, but the best part is he always starts from the most basic concept. This has helped me get a much better understanding of how to apply a concept to an idea, I am just not sure about how clear my concept is.

narratives.question_text: Please offer additional comments on such topics as: what worked best about the course, suggested improvements, class materials, etc.
comments: Set times for some of the practical assignments. exercises can include more real life situations that the instructor has been a part of with reference to actual production problems.
